(104, 'Two beakers are similar. One holds 100 cl and the other 200 cl. The 200 cl jug is 20 cm high. What is the height of the 100 cl beaker?', '$15.9 cm$', '$15.7 cm$', '$15 cm$', NULL, 'choice_a', 'module', 'Mathematics', 1, 'Similarity & Congruence', 0, 'If the two jugs are similar, their heights are in the ratio of the cube roots of the volumes:\r\n\r\n\\[\r\n\\ \\sqrt{\\frac{V_1}{V_2}} = \\frac{h_1}{h_2} \r\n\\]\r\n\r\nHere, $V_2 = 200cl,\\ V_1\\ = 100cl,\\ h_1 = 20cm$\r\n\r\n\\[ \\begin{aligned} \r\n\r\n\\sqrt[3]{\\frac{100}{200}} = \\frac{h_1}{20} \\\\\r\nh_1 = \\frac{20}{\\sqrt[3]{2}} \\\\\r\nh_1 = 15.86 \\approx 15.9cm\r\n\\end{aligned} \\]', '2014-10-17 13:44:11', '2014-10-26 14:12:41', 'NULL', 'NULL', 0, NULL, 'NULL', 'NULL', 0, NULL, 'NULL', 'NULL', 0, NULL, 'NULL', 'NULL', 0, NULL, 'NULL', 'NULL', 0, NULL, 'NULL', 'NULL', 0, NULL),
